    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Fuel System - Disassembly</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Disassembly</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="1">
            <title>Fuel Filter Header Assembly</title>
            <para>It is not recommended to disassemble the fuel filter beyond circumstances involving periodic servicing
                that include the following:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel filter element replacement</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel strainer</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Sensor replacements (if determined by a DTC)</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>The fuel filter assembly can and should be disassembled if any of the following issues have been
                observed:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Contaminated fuel has been introduced to the engine, resulting in poor performance.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel or air leaks involving the priming pump assembly.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <figure id="f2651202" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH11/H11002.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="448px"
                         scalefitheight="532px"/>
                <caption>Fuel filter assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Housing cover</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring gasket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter element</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Post</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel pressure regulator assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Outlet gasket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Plug or EFP sensor (optional)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter housing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel strainer</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bowl O-ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel bowl (with heater option)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Drain valve</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel fitting</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Primer pump seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Water drain valve assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Self tapping screw (4)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Cartridge check valve</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retainer ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Primer pump assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 20 (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Water In Fuel (WIF) sensor</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fitting assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the fuel filter header assembly is to be disassembled, the following assembly details
                        should be noted in accordance with the above illustration:
                    </para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Lubricate threads of fuel bowl (item 11).</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Lubricate O-ring gasket (item 2).</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Lubricate threads and O-ring of Water In Fuel (WIF) sensor (item 21).</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Lubricate threads and O-ring on drain valve (item 12).</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>
                                <hotlnk document="eges2651_249.xml" xrefid="t2651202" appearance="hottext">Torque values
                                    for illustration items appear in
                                </hotlnk>
                                .
                            </para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
